Key Benefits of Platform-Specific Payloads
1. Optimal User Experience
Mobile Users Get:
â”œâ”€â”€ Quick, scannable content
â”œâ”€â”€ Essential information only  
â”œâ”€â”€ Optimized for small screens
â””â”€â”€ Touch-friendly interactions

Desktop Users Get:
â”œâ”€â”€ Rich, detailed content
â”œâ”€â”€ Full context and information
â”œâ”€â”€ Professional presentation
â””â”€â”€ Multiple interaction options
2. Platform-Native Design
Mobile Characteristics:
â”œâ”€â”€ Short titles (â‰¤25 chars)
â”œâ”€â”€ Brief body (â‰¤20 chars)
â”œâ”€â”€ Deep link actions
â””â”€â”€ Mobile-optimized UX

Desktop Characteristics:
â”œâ”€â”€ Descriptive titles (â‰¤100 chars)
â”œâ”€â”€ Detailed body (â‰¤300 chars)
â”œâ”€â”€ Rich visual elements (icons, headers)
â”œâ”€â”€ Interactive buttons
â””â”€â”€ Professional presentation
3. Client Control
Application Benefits:
â”œâ”€â”€ Complete control over content per platform
â”œâ”€â”€ No automatic truncation or transformation
â”œâ”€â”€ Platform-optimized messaging strategies  
â”œâ”€â”€ Consistent with platform design patterns
â””â”€â”€ Explicit targeting reduces surprises
4. Clear Separation of Concerns
Platform Responsibilities:
â”œâ”€â”€ Mobile: Quick alerts and notifications
â”œâ”€â”€ Desktop: Rich information and actions
â”œâ”€â”€ Each optimized for its context
â””â”€â”€ No compromise solutions
This platform-specific payload approach ensures that each platform gets content that's specifically crafted for its strengths and user expectations, resulting in the best possible user experience across all devices.

Explain in this  Flow: Namespace â†’ Schema â†’ Routes â†’ Capabilities â†’ Notifications

Complete Flow: Namespace â†’ Schema â†’ Routes â†’ Capabilities â†’ Notifications
