do we need "jobs to be done" list associated with capabilities?   no code

Jobs-to-be-Done (JTBD) for Notification Platform Capabilities
ğŸ¯ Why JTBD for Capabilities?
Current Problem
Without JTBD, we have:
â”œâ”€â”€ Generic capability names: "book_a_seat", "learning_assignment"
â”œâ”€â”€ Unclear business value: Why does this capability exist?
â”œâ”€â”€ Missing context: What job is the user trying to accomplish?
â”œâ”€â”€ Poor prioritization: Which capabilities matter most to business?
â””â”€â”€ Limited innovation: Hard to identify gaps or opportunities
With JTBD, we get
Clear business purpose:
â”œâ”€â”€ User context: When I'm [situation], I want to [motivation], so I can [outcome]
â”œâ”€â”€ Success metrics: How do we measure if the job is done well?
â”œâ”€â”€ Priority clarity: Which jobs are most critical to business success?
â”œâ”€â”€ Innovation roadmap: What jobs aren't being served well?
â””â”€â”€ Platform evolution: How should capabilities evolve based on job success?
ğŸ“‹ JTBD Framework for Capabilities
Capability Structure with JTBD
CAPABILITY: book_a_seat
â”œâ”€â”€ Primary Job: "When I need workspace for tomorrow, I want immediate confirmation, so I can plan my day confidently"
â”œâ”€â”€ Secondary Jobs: 
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ "When my booking changes, I want to know immediately, so I can adjust my schedule"
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ "When I book a desk, I want colleagues to know where I am, so we can collaborate easily"
â”œâ”€â”€ Success Metrics: Booking confidence, schedule planning efficiency, collaboration facilitation
â”œâ”€â”€ User Personas: Hybrid workers, team leads, project collaborators
â””â”€â”€ Business Value: Office space optimization, employee satisfaction, collaboration improvement
ğŸ¯ Example: Learning Assignment JTBD Analysis
Primary Jobs to be Done
Job 1: Compliance Confidence
JOB STATEMENT: "When I get assigned training, I want clear deadlines and progress tracking, so I can stay compliant without stress"

USER PERSONA: Busy employee (John)
SITUATION: Multiple training assignments with different deadlines
MOTIVATION: Avoid compliance violations and associated consequences
DESIRED OUTCOME: Complete all training on time without last-minute panic

SUCCESS METRICS:
â”œâ”€â”€ On-time completion rate: >95%
â”œâ”€â”€ Employee stress indicators: Low anxiety about compliance
â”œâ”€â”€ Last-minute completions: <10% of all completions
â””â”€â”€ Employee satisfaction: High confidence in compliance status

CURRENT CAPABILITY SUPPORT:
âœ… learning_assignment: Provides clear initial assignment
âœ… learning_reminder: Proactive deadline management
âœ… learning_escalation: Safety net for missed deadlines
Job 2: Team Compliance Management
JOB STATEMENT: "When managing a team, I want visibility into training status, so I can ensure team compliance without micromanaging"

USER PERSONA: Team Manager (Sarah)
SITUATION: Responsible for team compliance but not involved in day-to-day training
MOTIVATION: Meet compliance requirements while maintaining trust with team
DESIRED OUTCOME: Team stays compliant with minimal manager intervention

SUCCESS METRICS:
â”œâ”€â”€ Team compliance rate: >98%
â”œâ”€â”€ Manager intervention frequency: Minimal escalations needed
â”œâ”€â”€ Manager confidence: High visibility into team status
â””â”€â”€ Employee autonomy: Self-managed compliance without feeling monitored

CURRENT CAPABILITY SUPPORT:
âœ… learning_escalation: Automatic manager notifications when needed
â“ POTENTIAL NEW CAPABILITY: team_compliance_dashboard
â“ POTENTIAL NEW CAPABILITY: proactive_team_insights
Job 3: Organizational Learning Culture
JOB STATEMENT: "When promoting continuous learning, I want to celebrate achievements and encourage growth, so learning becomes part of company culture"

USER PERSONA: HR/L&D Professional (Lisa)
SITUATION: Moving from compliance-only to learning culture
MOTIVATION: Transform training from burden to competitive advantage
DESIRED OUTCOME: Employees actively seek learning opportunities

SUCCESS METRICS:
â”œâ”€â”€ Voluntary training enrollment: Increasing trend
â”œâ”€â”€ Training completion enthusiasm: High engagement scores
â”œâ”€â”€ Peer learning: Employees sharing knowledge gained
â””â”€â”€ Business impact: Skills applied to improve work outcomes

CURRENT CAPABILITY SUPPORT:
âœ… learning_completion: Celebrates individual achievements
â“ POTENTIAL NEW CAPABILITY: peer_learning_sharing
â“ POTENTIAL NEW CAPABILITY: learning_impact_stories
â“ POTENTIAL NEW CAPABILITY: voluntary_learning_recommendations
ğŸ“Š JTBD-Driven Capability Development
Capability Priority Matrix
HIGH BUSINESS IMPACT + HIGH USER NEED:
â”œâ”€â”€ learning_assignment: Core compliance job
â”œâ”€â”€ learning_reminder: Proactive stress reduction
â”œâ”€â”€ book_a_seat: Essential workspace planning
â””â”€â”€ meeting_reminder: Critical schedule management

