### **Q12: How much does this cost compared to each app building its own notifications?**

**ANSWER:** "Like buying groceries at a big store vs each family growing their own food - shared infrastructure is much more efficient"
INDIVIDUAL APPROACH COSTS:

EACH APP BUILDS OWN SYSTEM:
â”œâ”€â”€ MyWorkspace team: 6 months, 3 developers = $450K
â”œâ”€â”€ HR app team: 4 months, 2 developers = $300K
â”œâ”€â”€ Banking app team: 8 months, 4 developers = $600K
â”œâ”€â”€ 10 other apps: Average $400K each = $4M
â””â”€â”€ Total development: $5.35M + ongoing maintenance

ONGOING COSTS PER APP:
â”œâ”€â”€ Server infrastructure: $5K/month per app
â”œâ”€â”€ Developer maintenance: 0.5 developer per app
â”œâ”€â”€ Support and troubleshooting: $2K/month per app
â”œâ”€â”€ Total per app: $12K/month
â””â”€â”€ 13 apps Ã— $12K = $156K/month = $1.87M/year

SHARED PLATFORM APPROACH:

ONE-TIME PLATFORM BUILD:
â”œâ”€â”€ Platform development: 12 months, 8 developers = $1.2M
â”œâ”€â”€ Integration support: 6 months, 2 developers = $300K
â”œâ”€â”€ Total development: $1.5M (vs $5.35M individual)
â””â”€â”€ Savings: $3.85M in development costs

ONGOING PLATFORM COSTS: â”œâ”€â”€ Platform infrastructure: $25K/month for all apps â”œâ”€â”€ Platform team: 3 developers = $45K/month
â”œâ”€â”€ Support and operations: $10K/month â”œâ”€â”€ Total platform: $80K/month = $960K/year â””â”€â”€ Savings: $910K/year in ongoing costs

BUSINESS CASE:
â”œâ”€â”€ Development savings: $3.85M
â”œâ”€â”€ Annual operational savings: $910K
â”œâ”€â”€ Payback period: 18 months
â”œâ”€â”€ 5-year savings: $8.4M
â””â”€â”€ Plus: Better user experiences, faster time to market


