### **Q15: What happens when we want to add new types of notifications?**

**ANSWER:** "Easy to add new capabilities - like adding new recipes to a cookbook"
ADDING NEW CAPABILITY:

BUSINESS REQUEST:
"We need to notify managers when their team members complete training, so they can provide recognition and plan advanced learning"

PLATFORM PROCESS:

STEP 1: Define the capability
â”œâ”€â”€ Capability name: "team_learning_completion"
â”œâ”€â”€ Business purpose: Manager recognition and development planning
â”œâ”€â”€ Success outcome: Managers acknowledge completions within 24 hours
â”œâ”€â”€ Target users: All people managers (about 2,500 users)
â””â”€â”€ Priority: Medium (improves learning culture)

STEP 2: Map to existing infrastructure
â”œâ”€â”€ Mobile namespace: Quick manager notification
â”œâ”€â”€ Desktop namespace: Full team dashboard integration
â”œâ”€â”€ Email namespace: Weekly team summary option
â”œâ”€â”€ Teams namespace: Channel celebration posting
â””â”€â”€ All platforms already exist - just new capability routing

STEP 3: Create platform-specific experiences
â”œâ”€â”€ Mobile: "John completed Cybersecurity training ğŸ‰"
â”œâ”€â”€ Desktop: Full completion details + next course recommendations
â”œâ”€â”€ Email: Weekly digest with all team completions
â”œâ”€â”€ Teams: Auto-post celebration in team channel
â””â”€â”€ Each platform optimized for manager context

STEP 4: Deploy and measure
â”œâ”€â”€ Test with pilot group of 50 managers
â”œâ”€â”€ Measure: Manager engagement, recognition frequency, team satisfaction
â”œâ”€â”€ Optimize based on feedback
â”œâ”€â”€ Roll out to all managers
â””â”€â”€ Track success metrics ongoing

RESULT:
â”œâ”€â”€ New capability added in 2-3 weeks
â”œâ”€â”€ No changes needed to existing applications
â”œâ”€â”€ Managers get better team insights
â”œâ”€â”€ Employees get more recognition
â””â”€â”€ Learning culture improves measurably


