â”œâ”€â”€ Each user profile includes time zone setting
â”œâ”€â”€ All notifications scheduled in user's local time
â”œâ”€â”€ Business hours respected per location
â”œâ”€â”€ Quiet hours calculated locally
â””â”€â”€ Meeting reminders account for user location

GLOBAL COORDINATION:
â”œâ”€â”€ Central system time (UTC) for consistency
â”œâ”€â”€ Local time conversion for delivery
â”œâ”€â”€ Cross-timezone meeting notifications handled intelligently
â”œâ”€â”€ Follow-the-sun support coverage
â””â”€â”€ Regional compliance with local regulations

EXAMPLE SCENARIOS:

GLOBAL TRAINING ASSIGNMENT: â”œâ”€â”€ Sent simultaneously to all employees worldwide â”œâ”€â”€ London user: Receives at 9 AM GMT â”œâ”€â”€ New York user: Receives at 9 AM EST
â”œâ”€â”€ Tokyo user: Receives at 9 AM JST â”œâ”€â”€ Content localized to each user's language â””â”€â”€ Due dates adjusted for local business calendars

URGENT SYSTEM MAINTENANCE:
â”œâ”€â”€ Critical alert needs immediate global delivery
â”œâ”€â”€ Overrides quiet hours (with user permission)
